- id: "ability:submerged_stealth#hunter_flood_flourisher"
  name: "Submerged Stealth"
  label: null
  type: null
  description: "At 8th level, a flood flourisher learns how to ambush targets from\
    \ beneath the muck, becoming a silent threat. While in a deep bog, the flood flourisher\
    \ can use cover from the water to attempt Stealth checks with no penalties from\
    \ the natural environment.\nWhile in a deep bog, as long as she moves no more\
    \ than 5 feet in a round, she has tremorsense out to a range of 30 feet against\
    \ anything that moves within the same body of water. While underwater in a deep\
    \ bog, she can hold her breath for a number of minutes equal to 6 times her Constitution\
    \ score before she risks drowning."
  effects: null
  prerequisites: null
  source: "Pathfinder Player Companion: People of the Wastes"
